                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors; two groups of lines on the incipit page of the text, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section of the text; name of Hebrew letter in Ps. 118 (fol. 32ra); abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some other words, e.g., ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 3vb, 4ra), nǝbäl (e.g., fols. 4rb, 5rb), halle luya (e.g., fols. 5vb, 6ra), qǝdmä wangel (e.g., fols. 33rb, 36rb), wä-ʾәmzә (e.g., fols. 33vb, 46vb), mǝʿǝraf (fol. 49vb).</rubric>
